<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="953" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1A/105: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-02T18:00:00-05:00">October 2, 1937—6
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>407. Your 619, September 28, 6 p.m. There is no objection to inclusion of an
                        Agenda item concerning American Sugar Act for the stated purposes.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
